ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Kayunga district is approximately 75 kilometers to the Northeast of
Kampala, bordering the Victoria Nile river and distant from the Sudan
border where the most recent yellow fever activity has been reported (see
ProMED-mail postings below on yellow fever in Uganda. A good map of Uganda
is available at:
<http://www.reliefweb.int/w/map.nsf/0/BFFF0FA67A1CDD7985256CDB005A04CC?Opendocument>)
While Uganda is in the yellow fever endemic belt of Africa, this is the
first report of yellow fever from Uganda carried on ProMED-mail. More
information on this outbreak would be appreciated. - Mod.MPP]
